# jemdoc: menu{MENU}{useful.html}
= Useful links

== 👨‍💻 Recommended open-source softwares 
- [http://www.gnu.org/software/octave/ Octave] - Free alternative to MATLAB, with a language that is mostly compatible.
    -- [https://github.com/jupyter-xeus/xeus-octave/ xeus-octave] - Jupyter kernel for Octave
- [https://mathics.github.io/ Mathics] - Free alternative to Mathematica, with a language that is mostly compatible.
- [http://matheclipse.org/] - computer algebra language and Java symbolic math library.
- [http://peterwittek.com/sdp-in-python.html Semidefinite programming in Python] - A collection of Python libraries that can be used to solve LMIs and other optimization problems.
- [https://github.com/python-control/python-control Python-Control] - Python module that implements basic operations for analysis and design of feedback control systems.
- [https://github.com/ilayn/harold Harold] - Another open-source systems and controls toolbox for Python3.
- [https://github.com/JuliaControl/ControlSystems.jl] - Control system toolbox for [Julia https://julialang.org/].
- [https://github.com/WolframResearch/GurobiLink GurobiLink] - Gurobi interface with Wolfram Language.

== 🏫 Didactic and drawing resources
=== 🚴 Control theory

- [https://resourcium.org/] - A collection of control and automation resources. 

- [http://janismac.github.io/ControlChallenges/] - Simulate some control algorithms to different control problems in Javascript.

- [http://www2.ual.es/icontrol/ Automatic Control with Interactive Tools] - Course with free and interactive software.

- [https://icct.cafre.unipi.it/ Interactive course for control theory] - Course with interactive Jupyter notebooks.

- [https://lpsa.swarthmore.edu/Animations/] - Javascript tool for animation of linear physical systems

- [https://github.com/Nukleon84/pyflowsheet] - Python package to create process flow diagrams (PFD)

- [http://www.nonlinearbenchmark.org/index.html] - Database of systems for benchmarking nonlinear system identification algorithms.

- [https://cheever.domains.swarthmore.edu/] - Interactive demos for teaching classical control of linear systems.

- [https://demonstrations.wolfram.com/topic.html?topic=Control+Theory&limit=20] - Mathematica demonstrations related to control theory.

- [https://github.com/MathWorks-Teaching-Resources/Virtual-Controls-Laboratory] - Collection of virtual control laboratories implemented on Simulink.  

- [https://unilabs.dia.uned.es/] - A network formed by many universities that share their laboratory resources for education purposes.

- 📺 YouTube Channels:
  -- [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCTA4wwZkqdBS1CyQR_g6ntw/] - Prof. Luis Aguirre (UFMG), Portuguese only
  -- [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCm5mt-A4w61lknZ9lCsZtBw/] - Prof. Steve Brunton
  -- [https://www.youtube.com/user/ControlLectures] - Brian Douglas channel
  
- 📚 Free books:
  -- [https://openaccess.blucher.com.br/article-list/9786555502237-591/list Engenharia de Controle: Teoria e Prática] (Portuguese only)
  -- [http://mtm.ufsc.br/~aleitao/public/reprints/book2008-bl-9788524402715.pdf Introdução Teoria de Controle e Programação Dinâmica] (Portuguese only)
  -- [http://motion.me.ucsb.edu/book-ctds/ Contraction Theory for Dynamical Systems]
  -- [http://motion.me.ucsb.edu/book-lns/ Lectures on Network Systems]

- [http://controlcartoons.com/] - A cartoon tour of control theory

- [http://www-lab22.kuee.kyoto-u.ac.jp/%7Ehagiwara/diagraph/man-dia/man-dia.html DiaGraph] - Useful to draw block diagrams:
