=== 🤖 Robotics

- [https://www.robotarium.gatech.edu/ Robotarium project] - A remotely accessible swarm robotics research platform that remains freely accessible to anyone.

- [https://gym.offworld.ai/ OFFWORLD GYM] - Open-access physical robotics environment for real-world reinforcement learning benchmarking and research.

- [https://roboton.io/ roboton.io] - Roboton.io is a virtual robot-competition platform that can be used entirely from the browser.

=== 🔋Electronics
- [https://wokwi.com/ Wokwi] - Simulate circuits in your browser.

- [https://www.withdiode.com/ Diode] - 3D circuit simulator. Can be used to program Arduino boards. 

- [https://www.falstad.com/circuit/] - Online analog circuit simulator

- [https://kazuhikoarase.github.io/simcirjs/ simcirjs] - Digital circuit simulator in HTML5 and Javascript

- [http://digitaljs.tilk.eu/ Yosys2digitaljs] - Online SystemVerilog synthetizer

- [https://github.com/xesscorp/skidl SKiDL] - SKiDL is a module that allows you to compactly describe the interconnection of electronic circuits and components using Python. 

- [https://github.com/formatc1702/WireViz Wireviz] - WireViz is a tool for easily documenting cables, wiring harnesses and connector pinouts. It takes plain text, YAML-formatted files as input and produces beautiful graphical output

=== 🧰 Miscellaneous

- [https://github.com/SamLau95/nbinteract nbinteract] - Generate Interactive Web Pages From Jupyter Notebooks. See also this [https://elc.github.io/posts/embed-interactive-notebooks/ tutorial].

- [https://github.com/damianavila/RISE RISE] - Turn Jupyter notebooks into slideshow

- [https://observablehq.com/ ObservableHQ] - Interactive notebooks with Javascript. For an interesting example, see [this notebook](https://observablehq.com/@patrickmineault/stabilizing-the-cart-pole-inverse-pendulum-using-lqr). 

- [https://jupyterbook.org/intro.html Jupyter{book}] - Build books with Jupyter

- [https://github.com/unconed/mathbox MathBox] - Presentation-quality WebGL math graphing
 (see also [https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/znah/mathbox/blob/jupyter/examples/notebooks/mathbox.ipynb?flush_cache=true How to use Jupyter with MathBox2 plots])

- [https://www.eulertour.com/ EulerTool] - Online editor for Manim, an animation engine for explanatory math videos 

- [https://github.com/krassowski/jupyter-manim Jupyter-Manim] - Jupyter notebook magic to integrate manim within output cells. 

- [https://mathinspector.com/ Math Inspector] - A visual programming environment for scientific computing.

- [https://cindyjs.org/ CindyJS] - A framework to create interactive (mathematical) content for the web.

- [https://sagecell.sagemath.org/static/about.html SageMathCell] - SageMathCell can be used to embed Sage computations into any webpage.

- [https://demonstrations.wolfram.com/ Wolfram Demonstrations Project] - Database of interactive demonstrations made with Mathematica.

- [https://www.mathworks.com/products/matlab-grader.html  MATLAB Grader] - Automatically grade MATLAB code in any learning environment

- *For recording and creating online courses*:
  -- [https://www.grapic.co/] - Collaborate on real whiteboards and notebooks in remote and hybrid meetings.
  -- [https://sanas.ai/] - Allow speakers to speak in different accents
  -- [https://www.descript.com/] - Edit audio by editing text. (English only)
  -- [https://www.narakeet.com/] - Use markdown syntax to create video clips from images, add captions, and life-like narration audio from your text. (Has Portuguese narration)
  -- [https://www.synthesia.io/] - Automatically redub videos (and even edit the mouth movements) to other languages with A.I. 
  -- [https://www.clonedub.com/] - Convert audio into other languages using the same voices. Can be used to removed strong accent.

== 🔬 Open science and reproducibility resources
- [http://www.sherpa.ac.uk/romeoinfo.html SHERPA] - Database of publisher's archiving policies.
- [https://ieeeauthorcenter.ieee.org/create-your-ieee-article/use-authoring-tools-and-ieee-article-templates/about-managing-your-data/] - How to share your data and code on IEEE Xplore.
